Questions

1. In the sentence below, put in the necessary HTML code that would allow users to
click on the word Google and open Google's homepage in a new browser:

Google is the best search engine in the world.

 <a href="https://www.google.com" target="_blank">Google</a>


2. Describe the purpose of a div tag.

The purpose of a div tag is to group together HTML elements to style with CSS.


3. Write out the basic structure of an HTML page in its most basic form, putting
the basic tags in the correct position. (Note: you don't need to include the meta
charset, viewport meta tag, or connect it to a stylesheet.)

<!DOCTYPE html>

<html>

		<head>

			<title>Title Goes Here</title>

		</head>

		<body>

					This is a body paragraph.

		</body>

</html>


4. There are two main "areas" or "sections" in the basic structure of an HTML
page. In which area would you put a link to a stylesheet?

You would link a stylesheet in the head section.


5. In which main "area" or "section" of an HTML page would you put text, images or
DIV tags?

I would put content like text and images in the body section.


6. In the space below, put one div tag with a class of graphicbox and a second div
tag with an ID of boxname. (You don't need to write out CSS rules - I'm looking for
the correct HTML syntax.)

<div class=“graphicbox”>

		<div id=“boxname”></div>

</div>

7. In the space below, put ONE div tag with an ID of apples and a class of fruit.
(You don't need to write out CSS rules - I'm looking for the correct HTML syntax.)

<div id=“apples” class=“fruit”>

</div>

8. In the space below, write the correct CSS code to target a div with a class of
fruit in a stylesheet. Make the color of the text black (#000000).

.fruit {
color: #000000
}

9. What tag would we use to include an image on an HTML page? Just give me the
name of the tag, you don't have to write out all the code.

<img>

10. What is the main difference between a serif and a sans-serif font?

The edges of the letters. The edges of serif letters include decoration while the edges of sans-serif's letters have no decoration. 


11. Which of the following is a hexadecimal code? To answer, delete the options
that are not a hexadecimal code.
#FFCC33

12. What's the difference between margin and padding?

Margin is space outside of the border and padding is space between the content and the border.

13. Using shorthand CSS code, specify 10px for the top and bottom margins, 20px for
the left margin, and 30px for the right margin for this div:

div { 
margin: 10px 30px 10px 20px;
}

14. Name two graphic design principles.

proximity and repetition

15. Comment out the sentence below using an HTML comment.

Please comment me out using an HTML comment.

